{{神社 |Name = Suitengu (水天宮) |Image = [[File:Okinohata-suitengu02n.jpg|300px]] |Location = Inari Town, {{ill|Yanagawa City|ja|柳川市}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}} |Coordinates = {{Coord|33|09|31.5|N|130|23|42.5|E|region:JP-40_type:landmark_scale:25000|display=inline,title}} |Deity = {{ill|Emperor Antoku|ja|安徳天皇}} |Status = |Founded = {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治}} 2 ({{ill|1869|ja|1869th year }}) |Main Hall = |Alternate Names = Okinohata Suitengu, Suitengu-san |Votive Site = |Annual Festival = May 3–5 |Shinto Rituals = }}
'''Okinohata Suitengu''' (沖端水天宮) is a {{ill|Suitengu Shrine|ja|水天宮|lt=Shinto Shrine (Suitengu)|lt_ja=神社（水天宮）}} located in Inari Town, {{ill|Yanagawa City|ja|柳川市}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}}. The registered {{ill|Registration|ja|登記}} name under the {{ill|Religious Corporation|ja|宗教法人}} is '''Suitengu''' (すいてんぐう).
== 祭神 == * {{ill|Emperor Antoku|ja|安徳天皇}}
== 由緒 == {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治}} 2 ({{ill|1869|ja|1869th year }}) saw the enshrinement of the {{ill|Bunrei|ja|分霊}} from the head office – {{ill|Head Office|ja|本社|lt=General Head Office|lt_ja=総本社}} – of {{ill|Suitengu (Kurume City)|ja|水天宮 (久留米市)|lt=Kurume Suitengu|lt_ja=久留米水天宮}}, which was combined ({{ill|合祀|1=co-Enshrinement|2=ja|3=合祀}}) with the Inari Shrine ({{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社}}) and Yaken Shrine (弥剣神社（{{ill|Gion Shrine|ja|祇園社}}）) within the area to establish the shrine. In addition, the Inari Shrine was founded in {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄}} 3 ({{ill|1587|ja|1587th year }}) by {{ill|Tachibana Muneshige|ja|立花宗茂}}, while the Yaken Shrine was established during the {{ill|Bunka|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化}} period (1804–1818).
Locally, it is known as "'''Suitengu-san'''". During the Okinohata Suitengu Festival held on May 3, 4, and 5, a boat stage called Sangu-maru is constructed and the Suitengu festival music is performed from dusk.
== 祭事 == [[File:Fukuoka Yanagawa10s3.jpg|thumb|水天宮大祭]] * 2月初午日 初午祭 * 5月3～5日 水天宮大祭 * 7月20・21日 祇園祭
== Access == * {{ill|Nishinippon Railroad|ja|西日本鉄道|lt=Nishitetsu|lt_ja=西鉄}}{{ill|Nishitetsu Tenjin Ōmuta Line|ja|西鉄天神大牟田線|lt=Tenjin Ōmuta Line|lt_ja=天神大牟田線}}{{ill|Nishitetsu Yanagawa Station|ja|西鉄柳川駅|lt=Yanagawa Station|lt_ja=柳川駅}} – alight and then: ** Board the {{ill|Nishitetsu Bus|ja|西鉄バス}} bound for "Hayatsue" ("早津江"), alight at the "Suitengu Entrance" ("水天宮入口") bus stop; a 4‑minute walk. ** Alternatively, take the same bus bound for "Hayatsue" or the "Yanagawa Hospital Loop" ("柳川病院循環"), alight at the "Mihanae" ("御花前") bus stop; a 6‑minute walk. ** Board the {{ill|Horikawa Bus|ja|堀川バス}} bound for "Kanpo no Yado Yanagawa" ("かんぽの宿柳川"), alight at the final stop; an 8‑minute walk. ** Approximately 10 minutes by taxi from the station.
