'''Okinohata Suitengu''' (沖端水天宮) is a {{ill|Suitengu Shrine|ja|水天宮|lt=Shinto Shrine (Suitengu)|lt_ja=神社（水天宮）|12=draft|12=draft}} located in Inari Town, {{ill|Yanagawa City|ja|柳川市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|12=draft|12=draft}}. The registered {{ill|Registration|ja|登記|12=draft|12=draft}} name under the {{ill|Religious Corporation|ja|宗教法人|12=draft|12=draft}} is '''Suitengu''' (すいてんぐう).
== 祭神 == * {{ill|Emperor Antoku|ja|安徳天皇|1=Emperor Antoku|2=ja|3=安徳天皇|4=de|5=Antoku|12=draft|12=draft}}
== 由緒 == {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 ({{ill|1869|ja|1869th year|12=draft|12=draft}}) saw the enshrinement of the {{ill|Bunrei|ja|分霊|12=draft|12=draft}} from the head office – {{ill|Head Office|ja|本社|lt=General Head Office|lt_ja=総本社|12=draft|12=draft}} – of {{ill|Suitengu (Kurume City)|ja|水天宮 (久留米市)|lt=Kurume Suitengu|lt_ja=久留米水天宮|12=draft|12=draft}}, which was combined ({{ill|合祀|1=co-Enshrinement|2=ja|3=合祀|12=draft|12=draft}}) with the Inari Shrine ({{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft|12=draft}}) and Yaken Shrine (弥剣神社（{{ill|Gion Shrine|ja|祇園社|12=draft|12=draft}}）) within the area to establish the shrine. In addition, the Inari Shrine was founded in {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄|12=draft|12=draft}} 3 ({{ill|1587|ja|1587th year|12=draft|12=draft}}) by {{ill|Tachibana Muneshige|ja|立花宗茂|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the Yaken Shrine was established during the {{ill|Bunka|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化|12=draft|12=draft}} period (1804–1818).
Locally, it is known as "'''Suitengu-san'''". During the Okinohata Suitengu Festival held on May 3, 4, and 5, a boat stage called Sangu-maru is constructed and the Suitengu festival music is performed from dusk.
