== 由緒 == {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 2 ({{ill|1869|ja|1869th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1869|qq=}}) saw the enshrinement of the {{ill|Bunrei|ja|分霊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunrei|qq=}} from the head office – {{ill|Head Office|ja|本社|lt=General Head Office|lt_ja=総本社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head Office|qq=}} – of {{ill|Suitengu (Kurume City)|ja|水天宮 (久留米市)|lt=Kurume Suitengu|lt_ja=久留米水天宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suitengu (Kurume City)|qq=}}, which was combined ({{ill|合祀|1=co-Enshrinement|2=ja|3=合祀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/合祀|13=User:Immanuelle/co-Enshrinement|qq=}}) with the Inari Shrine ({{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inari Shrine|qq=}}) and Yaken Shrine (弥剣神社（{{ill|Gion Shrine|ja|祇園社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gion Shrine|qq=}}）) within the area to establish the shrine. In addition, the Inari Shrine was founded in {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunroku|qq=}} 3 ({{ill|1587|ja|1587th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1587|qq=}}) by {{ill|Tachibana Muneshige|ja|立花宗茂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tachibana Muneshige|qq=}}, while the Yaken Shrine was established during the {{ill|Bunka|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunka|qq=}} period (1804–1818).
Locally, it is known as "'''Suitengu-san'''". During the Okinohata Suitengu Festival held on May 3, 4, and 5, a boat stage called Sangu-maru is constructed and the Suitengu festival music is performed from dusk.
