{{神社 |Name = Suitengu (水天宮) |image = [[File:Okinohata-suitengu02n.jpg|300px]] |Location = Inari Town, {{ill|Yanagawa City|ja|柳川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yanagawa City|qq=}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuoka Prefecture|qq=}} |Coordinates = {{Coord|33|09|31.5|N|130|23|42.5|E|region:JP-40_type:landmark_scale:25000|display=inline,title}} |Deity = {{ill|Emperor Antoku|ja|安徳天皇|1=Emperor Antoku|2=ja|3=安徳天皇|4=de|5=Antoku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Antoku|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Antoku|qq=}} |Status = |Founded = {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 2 ({{ill|1869|ja|1869th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1869|qq=}}) |Main Hall = |Alternate Names = Okinohata Suitengu, Suitengu-san |Votive Site = |Annual Festival = May 3–5 |Shinto Rituals = }}
'''Okinohata Suitengu''' (沖端水天宮) is a {{ill|Suitengu Shrine|ja|水天宮|lt=Shinto Shrine (Suitengu)|lt_ja=神社（水天宮）|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suitengu Shrine|qq=}} located in Inari Town, {{ill|Yanagawa City|ja|柳川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yanagawa City|qq=}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuoka Prefecture|qq=}}. The registered {{ill|Registration|ja|登記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Registration|qq=}} name under the {{ill|Religious Corporation|ja|宗教法人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Religious Corporation|qq=}} is '''Suitengu''' (すいてんぐう).
== 祭神 == * {{ill|Emperor Antoku|ja|安徳天皇|1=Emperor Antoku|2=ja|3=安徳天皇|4=de|5=Antoku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Antoku|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Antoku|qq=}}
== 由緒 == {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 2 ({{ill|1869|ja|1869th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1869|qq=}}) saw the enshrinement of the {{ill|Bunrei|ja|分霊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunrei|qq=}} from the head office – {{ill|Head Office|ja|本社|lt=General Head Office|lt_ja=総本社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head Office|qq=}} – of {{ill|Suitengu (Kurume City)|ja|水天宮 (久留米市)|lt=Kurume Suitengu|lt_ja=久留米水天宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suitengu (Kurume City)|qq=}}, which was combined ({{ill|合祀|1=co-Enshrinement|2=ja|3=合祀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/合祀|13=User:Immanuelle/co-Enshrinement|qq=}}) with the Inari Shrine ({{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inari Shrine|qq=}}) and Yaken Shrine (弥剣神社（{{ill|Gion Shrine|ja|祇園社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gion Shrine|qq=}}）) within the area to establish the shrine. In addition, the Inari Shrine was founded in {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunroku|qq=}} 3 ({{ill|1587|ja|1587th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1587|qq=}}) by {{ill|Tachibana Muneshige|ja|立花宗茂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tachibana Muneshige|qq=}}, while the Yaken Shrine was established during the {{ill|Bunka|ja|文化 (元号)|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunka|qq=}} period (1804–1818).
Locally, it is known as "'''Suitengu-san'''". During the Okinohata Suitengu Festival held on May 3, 4, and 5, a boat stage called Sangu-maru is constructed and the Suitengu festival music is performed from dusk.
== 祭事 == [[File:Fukuoka Yanagawa10s3.jpg|thumb|水天宮大祭]] * 2月初午日 初午祭 * 5月3～5日 水天宮大祭 * 7月20・21日 祇園祭
== Access == * {{ill|Nishinippon Railroad|ja|西日本鉄道|lt=Nishitetsu|lt_ja=西鉄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishinippon Railroad|qq=}}{{ill|Nishitetsu Tenjin Ōmuta Line|ja|西鉄天神大牟田線|lt=Tenjin Ōmuta Line|lt_ja=天神大牟田線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishitetsu Tenjin Ōmuta Line|qq=}}{{ill|Nishitetsu Yanagawa Station|ja|西鉄柳川駅|lt=Yanagawa Station|lt_ja=柳川駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishitetsu Yanagawa Station|qq=}} – alight and then: ** Board the {{ill|Nishitetsu Bus|ja|西鉄バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishitetsu Bus|qq=}} bound for "Hayatsue" ("早津江"), alight at the "Suitengu Entrance" ("水天宮入口") bus stop; a 4‑minute walk. ** Alternatively, take the same bus bound for "Hayatsue" or the "Yanagawa Hospital Loop" ("柳川病院循環"), alight at the "Mihanae" ("御花前") bus stop; a 6‑minute walk. ** Board the {{ill|Horikawa Bus|ja|堀川バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikawa Bus|qq=}} bound for "Kanpo no Yado Yanagawa" ("かんぽの宿柳川"), alight at the final stop; an 8‑minute walk. ** Approximately 10 minutes by taxi from the station.
